   By STEVEN BUTLER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MITSUBISHI Electric, Japan's third-largest electric machinery maker,
yesterday reported a 73.7 per cent plunge in interim parent company pre-tax
profits to Y12.3bn (Dollars 100.8m), while sales fell by 4.5 per cent to
