FT  28 OCT 92 / Orkney social workers criticised
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
SOCIAL workers who removed nine children from their Orkney homes in dawn
raids during investigations into alleged sex abuse acted too soon and
without taking time to think, a judicial inquiry has found.
Lord Clyde, who headed the inquiry, said the social workers failed to
consider any other action and they and police should have made further
inquiries. He made 194 recommendations, including a call for new national
guidelines for dealing with child abuse.
