majority' of the recommendations.
The children's parents said they would bring a civil action for 'substantial
damages' for the trauma families suffered.
Orkney council chiefs said they were 'shocked and taken aback' by the
criticism. An emergency council meeting will be held on Friday and a team
set up to decide what action to take.
