<HEADLINE>
FT  28 OCT 92 / Parliament and Politics: Tory party opinion
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Major's decision to attend the 1922 meeting tomorrow has stymied an
initiative by backbench loyalists to set up a 'breakaway' committee which
would, they say, more accurately represent Tory party opinion at
Westminster. The loyalists had planned to boycott the regular meeting of the
'22 and hold their own discussion instead, to register disapproval of the
high public profile of Sir Marcus Fox, the committee's chairman. Whether the
planned breakaway is merely postponed or lapses will now depend on how
Thursday's meeting goes.
