<HEADLINE>
FT  28 OCT 92 / Woman to head Italian DC party
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ROME
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Italy's long-dominant Christian Democrats (DC), now struggling against
growing voter hostility, elected their first woman president yesterday to
shore up their battered image, Reuter reports from Rome. Mrs Rosa Russo
Jervolino is also education minister.
</TEXT>
<PUB>The Financial Times
</PUB>
<PAGE>
London Page 2
</PAGE>
