growth of other costs in test, assembly and procurement. The charge also
provided increased reserves for estimated work remaining on the programme.
Excluding the C-17, operating earnings in the company's military aerospace
business totalled Dollars 122m, up from Dollars 99m, thanks to increased
earnings from the F/A-18 Hornet, the AH-64 Apache and AV-8B Harrier
