FT  27 OCT 92 / BR set to improve Severn Tunnel safety
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
BRITISH RAIL is to carry out a wide range of safety and communications
improvements at the Severn Tunnel after the collision of two trains in which
nearly 100 passengers were injured.
Details will be given later this week to the public inquiry into the crash
which happened about a mile from the Welsh end of the tunnel last December.
